Defendant Joseph A Howell in court with attorney Jason C. Gonzalez.  Shawn N Woller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The State files an amended complaint in Court.     Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Counts 1, 2 and 3,  Court finds defendant guilty.  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

Count #1:

8 MONTHS JAIL; 

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEAR(S); (probation may be transferred to Dane County);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No contact with:   Victim, Roxane D. 
*Write letter of apology to victim;
*DNA Sample and surcharge waived, based on date of violation;
*Perform 100 hours of community service;

RESTITUTION:  $6000.00  payable to Roxane D. ($3500.00 paid upfront to the District Attorney's Office, apply $2500.00 cash bail)
COURT COSTS:  $253.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME: 45 DAYS, LAST 15 DAYS, STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.   Defendant to report no later than 6:00 p.m. on Tuesday, December 1, 2015.  (May be transferred to Dane Count but MAY NOT BE SERVED WITH ELECTRONIC MONITORING);


Count #2:

8 MONTHS JAIL; (CONSECUTIVE TO COUNT #1)


TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEAR(S);
 (probation may be transferred to Dane County);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
Same as Count #1;

COURT COSTS:  $243.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);


Count #3:

8 MONTHS JAIL; (CONSECUTIVE TO COUNTS #1 & #2)


TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEAR(S);
 (probation may be transferred to Dane County);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
Same as Counts #1 and #2

